p.s. if they stack, I'll be happy in xp groups.  I'm not sure it'll be worth an extra buff slot on a raid though :/ <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A> at: 12/3/01 4:20:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulotusflystewnicely.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lotusfly Stewnicely</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/4/01 6:38:56 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.prexus.com/ef/becky/snap.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Nature's Recovery</span><hr size=1> Nature's Recovery is not intended to unbalance the druid class by making us any more powerful.  It's intended to provide a little extra fun for the druid class.<br>
<br>
Nature's Touch:  400 mana, for 978 HP<br>
Nature's Recovery:  250 mana, for 900 HP, over 3 minutes.<br>
<br>
<br>
<b>Uses</b><br>
<br>
<i>Raids</I><br>
On raids, prior to a big fight, this is going to help the amount I can heal by a huge amount.  <br>
<br>
During the fight, you will be using your mana on Nature's Touch / Chloroblast (same efficiencies).  By casting Nature's Recovery prior to the fight, I get a higher regen on 2 of my party, which I can med up before the creature arrives.  Therefore, my healing power has increased.  Increases in healing power are good.<br>
<br>
Whilst in the fight, if a group member is damaged by a significant amount, and I know that the fight is going to last some time (a large number of end-game fights are over three minutes in length), then I can cast Nature's Recovery on them, and get the same amount of healing as if I had NT'd them, but for less mana.  Therefore, again, my healing power has increased.  As noted above, increases in my healing power are good.<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>Exp Groups</i><br>
<br>
With Luclin, we will all be exping with our guilds.  We'll be spending lots of time in groups with a constant flow of creatures coming in, and our party taking constant amounts of damage.  I can keep the group's top two melees, or maybe the enchanter if it is a chaotic spawn, regenerating at 30 HP/tick.  This makes my tanks happy, it reduces the amount which I have to spend healing with Nature's Touch, and it spaces out the times between Complete Heals on the primary.  This is a good thing.<br>
<br>
<br>
<B>Summary</b><br>
<br>
It's a nice spell.  It eats up a spell slot which is intended to cause a few strategic considerations.  The mana cost isn't going to go down; it already reduces the amount that you have to spend on NTs by a large amount.<br>
<br>
Take this spell to a Vulak fight (or any raid fight with a decent length, i.e. 3 mins or more), or an exp group, and have some fun playing with it.  <br>
<br>
If you don't like it, no one is forcing you to use it.  ^_^<br>
<br>
For good, alert druids, who need to squeeze as much out of their mana bar as they can, and whom like a little tactical consideration, it's a decent (and possibly most important of all, not unbalanced) spell.<br>
<br>
Lotusfly begins to regenerate!<br>
<br>
